      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "I don't know if I agree with you on this point:\r\nMy intention here was not to change the behaviour of `SplitHostPort(...)` (rather to gain access to the port portion of a socket address as a string).\r\nIf you for example take a look at [src/httpserver.cpp](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/a748782a11f0b23f8dcdf167f45d68c863524887/src/httpserver.cpp#L307&L308&L309) in `HTTPBindAddresses(...)` this function is used as follows:\r\n`uint16_t port{some_default_port};\r\nSplitHostPort(..., port, ...);`\r\nThe same can be seen in `src/bitcoin-cli.cpp` and `src/net.cpp`: the callers have already set default port value before calling this function.",
      "commit_id" : "96942e85051553366dea65a9474049097631fbe3",
      "created_at" : "2021-06-04T11:05:31Z",
