      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "I'm unsure if I agree, I think that a return in this case can be misleading, which is why I instead implemented [`HasInvalidPort(...)`](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/96942e85051553366dea65a9474049097631fbe3/src/util/strencodings.h#L86-L93).\r\nI think that the range of thinkable input strings would call for a much more involved error handling in order to not be misleading (Is missing port an invalid port? What about missing host portion? What error message would we print for `SplitHostPort(\"333.444.555.666:99999\", ...) -> false`?). ",
